    • AddProduct

      public boolean AddProduct(int barcode, String name, String type, String brand, String colour, String connectivity, int quantity, double originalCost, double retailPrice, String layout)
      This method will add a new keyboard to the stock by writing a new line to Stock.txt.
      Parameters:
      barcode - item barcode as integer.
      name - item name.
      type - keyboard type (gaming or standard).
      brand - item brand.
      colour - item colour.
      connectivity - item connectivity (if wired or wireless).
      quantity - item quantity left in stock.
      originalCost - price item was originally bought for.
      retailPrice - price item is being sold for.
      layout - the keyboard layout (US or UK).
      Returns:
      replicate - used to see if the item being added is currently in the stock file or not.

    • AddProduct

      public boolean AddProduct(int barcode, String name, String type, String brand, String colour, String connectivity, int quantity, double originalCost, double retailPrice, int buttonNo)
      This method will add a new mouse to the stock by writing a new line to Stock.txt.
      Parameters:
      barcode - item barcode as integer.
      name - item name.
      type - mouse type (gaming or standard).
      brand - item brand.
      colour - item colour.
      connectivity - item connectivity (if wired or wireless).
      quantity - item quantity left in stock.
      originalCost - price item was originally bought for.
      retailPrice - price item is being sold for.
      buttonNo - the number of buttons on the mouse.
      Returns:
      replicate - used to see if the item being added is currently in the stock file or not.
